EIS was also used to confirm successful preparation of the sensor. More specifically, Fig. 3B shows the impedance changes recorded during preparation of the modified electrode. The total electrode impedance is expressed as the electron-transfer resistance (R

                           et
                        ) in series with a parallel circuit of the double-layer capacitance (C

                           dl
                        ) and the Warburg impedance (Z

                           w
                        ). Similarly, the electrode resistance (Fig. 3B) was found to decrease upon modification of the GCE with the Fe/Zn-BTC@C-dots (curves a and b), and the resistance of the sensor decreased further when the DNA aptamer and the target thiamethoxam molecule became individually bound to the electrode (curves c and d). These results also indicate the successful preparation of the sensor.
